data.content:
**All your sync calls will throw at runtime in .NET 11.** The EF Core 11 Cosmos DB provider **fully removed** sync I/O — the opt-in you had in .NET 10 no longer exists.

Affected methods in your code:
- `ToList()` → use `await ToListAsync()`
- `First(...)` → use `await FirstAsync(...)`
- `Count()` → use `await CountAsync()`
- `SaveChanges()` → use `await SaveChangesAsync()`

Your repository needs to become async:

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

This will ripple up through all callers — every method that calls these needs to become `async Task` as well. There is no workaround; the Cosmos SDK is async-only and EF Core 11 no longer wraps it.
